  "doc_id": "26728",
  "text": "In explanation, this emerged outcome shows that there is negative relationship between number of children and marital satisfaction among married Iranian immigrants. These findings is in good agreement with findings of [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] and [CITATION_4] that noted the absence of children or an empty nest had positive correlation with marital satisfaction. Also these results is identical to results of Dillon, et.al (2010) that by conducting a meta-analysis research on collectivistic cultures found that presence and number of children has impact on marital satisfaction negatively. However, this finding is inconsistent with finding of [CITATION_5] . This researcher found that number of children is a significant predictor of marital satisfaction than to the other traits such as level of education and finance for Nigerian population.",
